    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"319088\">@Gioele Zardini</span> What have you thought about systems with spatial extent rather than time?</p>",
        "id": 203134803,
        "sender_full_name": "James Fairbanks",
        "timestamp": 1594143414
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"275927\">@James Fairbanks</span> That's something we are thinking about, also because it connects with resources in both time and space (something we would like to describe in co-design). I still have to understand how to do that though</p>",
        "id": 203135427,
        "sender_full_name": "Gioele Zardini",
        "timestamp": 1594143745
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>With regards to @James Fairbanks' question, Goldblatt gave a  modal S4 for spacetime</p>",
